  "response": "There are several complex reasons why civilians have found it difficult to leave Aleppo during the Syrian conflict:\n\n1. Safety concerns:\n- Dangerous escape routes\n- Active conflict zones\n- Risk of being caught in crossfire\n- Potential attacks during evacuation\n\n2. Limited resources:\n- Lack of transportation\n- Financial constraints\n- Physical disabilities\n- No means to support travel\n\n3. Personal attachments:\n- Family ties\n- Property and belongings\n- Emotional connection to hometown\n- Unwillingness to abandon their homes\n\n4. Restricted movement:\n- Military checkpoints\n- Controlled exit routes\n- Limited humanitarian corridors\n- Potential persecution\n\n5. Uncertainty about destination:\n- Fear of refugee camps\n- Concerns about living conditions elsewhere\n- Potential discrimination\n- Uncertain future\n\n6. Humanitarian crisis:\n- Siege conditions\n- Limited access to food and medical supplies\n- No alternative shelter\n- Complex logistics of mass evacuation\n\nThese factors combined have made it extremely challenging for many civilians to leave Aleppo during the prolonged Syrian conflict, trapping them in dangerous environments with limited options for escape.",
